cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CYBER. 

This paper involves social media analysis and information retrieval, which are key components of the sub-categories cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Sociological Aspects of Technology). The paper also uses statistical modeling and recommendation algorithms, which fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with privacy and security concerns related to social media, which is relevant to cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
